{"title": "Carolina Chansons: Legends of the Low Country", "description": "This is a collection of poems about Charleston and the South Carolina Lowcountry.  DuBose Heyward was a Charleston native best known for his novel <i>Porgy</i>, which was the basis for the Gershwin opera <i>Porgy and Bess</i>.  Hervey Allen, who later wrote <i>Anthony Adverse</i>, met Heyward after moving to Charleston to teach.  Together they founded the Poetry Society of South Carolina, which is still active today.  (Summary by Laurie Anne Walden)", "duration": 6768, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "3361", "name": "Hervey Allen"}, {"id": "3360", "name": "DuBose Heyward"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt23/carolinachansons_1210.jpg", "copyright_year": "1922", "genres": ["Poetry"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Laurie Anne Walden"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Laurie Anne Walden"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Laurie Anne Walden"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Betty M."}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Acknowledgments and Preface", "readers": [1066], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/carolinachansons_1210_librivox/carolinachansons_01_heyward_64kb.mp3", "duration": 258}, {"section": 2, "title": "Seance at Sunrise; Silences; Presences", "readers": [1066], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/carolinachansons_1210_librivox/carolinachansons_02_heyward_64kb.mp3", "duration": 512}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Pirates", "readers": [1066], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/carolinachansons_1210_librivox/carolinachansons_03_heyward_64kb.mp3", "duration": 696}, {"section": 4, "title": "The Sewees of Sewee Bay; La Fayette Lands", "readers": [1066], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/carolinachansons_1210_librivox/carolinachansons_04_heyward_64kb.mp3", "duration": 536}, {"section": 5, "title": "The Priest and the Pirate: A Ballad of Theodosia Burr", "readers": [1066], "path": "https://www.